Feature: Files Download

  Background:
    Given I am authenticated

  Scenario: Download file successfully

    Given the following file exists in the database:
    """
    {
      "id": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850",
      "itemId": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846",
      "fileName": "document.pdf",
      "urlS3": "https://bucket.s3.amazonaws.com/items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_document.pdf",
      "size": 1024,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-31T10:00:00Z"
    }
    """

    Given the file "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_document.pdf" exists in S3

    When I GET "/api/v1/file/download/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850"
    Then the response status code should be 200
    Then the response header "Content-Disposition" should contain "attachment; filename=\"document.pdf\""
    Then the response header "Content-Type" should be "application/octet-stream"
    Then the response body should be binary content

  Scenario: Download file that does not exist

    When I GET "/api/v1/file/download/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a9999"
    Then the response status code should be 404

  Scenario: Download file with special characters in name

    Given the following file exists in the database:
    """
    {
      "id": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850",
      "itemId": "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846",
      "fileName": "relatório-financeiro-2026.pdf",
      "urlS3": "https://bucket.s3.amazonaws.com/items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_relatório-financeiro-2026.pdf",
      "size": 2048,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-31T10:00:00Z"
    }
    """

    Given the file "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_relatório-financeiro-2026.pdf" exists in S3

    When I GET "/api/v1/file/download/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850"
    Then the response status code should be 200
    Then the response header "Content-Disposition" should contain "attachment; filename=\"relatório-financeiro-2026.pdf\""

